The paper deals with solving extensive-form games using the counterfactual-regret minimization (CFR) framework, which is a popular approach in game theory and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the convergence rate of the proposed algorithm, which falls under the category of optimization and learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a likely category as well. The paper also uses simplex minimizers, which are commonly used in optimization and computational geometry, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible category. Finally, the paper discusses the refinement properties of Nash equilibrium, which is a topic in social choice theory, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) a possible category.
